JAPANESE ENCEPHALITIS AND OTHER - INDIA (16): (UTTAR PRADESH, BIHAR)
********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Thu 2 Sep 2010
Source: Chennaionline.com [edited]
<http://news.chennaionline.com/newsitem.aspx?NEWSID=877128f5-f586-4779-a832-935dd0bba6fc&CATEGORYNAME=NATL>


9 more persons today succumbed to Japanese encephalitis, taking the
toll in Uttar Pradesh's eastern region to 231, officials said. The 9
were undergoing treatment at BRD Medical College Hospital here,
Additional Director (Health) U K Srivastava said. Of the deceased, 4
hailed from Gorakhpur, 2 from Kushinagar and one each from Sant Kabir
Nagar and Siddharth Nagar. One victim hailed from neighbouring Bihar,
Srivastava said.

As many as 26 encephalitis patients have been admitted in BRD Medical
Hospital since yesterday [1 Sep 2010]. At present, 227 patients were
being treated in various government hospitals.

--
Communicated by:
HealthMap Alerts via ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of deaths has increased from 215 on 28 Aug 2010 to 231 in
this report (2 Sep 2010). Previous reports indicate that the majority
of these encephalitis cases are not caused by Japanese encephalitis
virus (JEV) infections, but the above report attributes all of them
to JEV. The virus(es) involved in the non-JEV cases have not been
specified, but may be enteroviruses.

A map showing the locations of the Indian states can be accessed at
<http://www.indianorphanages.net/images/india-political-map.gif>.
The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of India is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/02lp>. - Mod.TY]
